'''Captain Rabid Jack''' is the single most feared pirate of the [[Eastern Sea]]. Very little is known about him as almost no people dare to speak of the infamous Rabid Jack,{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Braindeath|loc=Rum Deal|quote=Rabid Jack! THE Rabid Jack! Egad... I haven't heard that name... before.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Brother Tranquillity|loc=The Great Brain Robbery|quote=One of the pirates on the island said [Jack's name] while in the grip of a terrible fever. The others quietened him down and refused to answer any questions about it. I have no doubt they know who it is, but I get the feeling that they will not tell you.}} but he apparently terrorised the Eastern Sea and its islands such as [[Mos Le'Harmless]]. He has, however, not been seen for years, and currently appears to reside somewhere near a temple in the Eastern Sea where he practises [[necromancy]], resurrecting [[zombie pirate]]s to expand his crew and plotting his return.{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Donnie|loc=Rum Deal|quote=After we take the island I'll have the boss haul yer body to the temple and... Err, never mind.}} It is suggested that this hideout is located beneath the sea.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mi-Gor|loc=The Great Brain Robbery|quote=*Wheeze* I have received a summons to attend to the Captain and so will be 'down below' for a while.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Brother Tranquillity|loc=The Great Brain Robbery|quote=Yes, one of the brothers observed him and a few of his sorebones slipping into the water shortly after there was a loud bang from inside the building.}}

Rabid Jack is responsible for sending [[Captain Donnie]] and his crew to invade [[Braindeath Island]] to plunder the island's production of [[Braindeath 'rum']] and kill all the [[brewer]]s. He also sent the undead Surgeon General [[Mi-Gor]] to invade [[Harmony Island]] and to conduct experiments on the residing [[Monk (Harmony Island)|monks]] to find a way to enhance his zombies by giving them un-rotting brains.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mi-Gor|loc=The Great Brain Robbery|quote=*Wheeze* Excellent... the gas will leave the brain intact for the next stage. *Wheeze* This time there will be no rebellion amongst the subjects. *Wheeze* Rabid Jack will have his crew of enhanced zombies and I will have as many test subjects as I can vivisect! *Wheeze* Hekhekhekhek!}} In sending his lackeys, Jack appears to be trying to conceal his own involvement in these events.{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Donnie|loc=Rum Deal|quote=Besides, Rabid Jack would have my hide if I told ye it were him that sent me!}} The [[player character|player]] managed to thwart both plots during the [[Rum Deal]] and [[The Great Brain Robbery]] quests.

